  "text": "Further, Zhan et al. [CITATION_1] 17 equips text synthesis with other deep learning techniques to produce more realistic samples. They introduce selective semantic segmentation so that word instances would only appear on sensible objects, e.g. a desk or wall in stead of someone's face. Text rendering in their work is adapted to the image so that they fit into the artistic styles and do not stand out awkwardly.",
